http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Fog-cover-shrouds-Delhi-NCR/article14008778.ece

Dense fog continued to affect flight schedules at the Delhi airport on Tuesday with almost 50 flights getting delayed by more than an hour.Tuesday also saw the second lowest day temperature this winter, coupled with high humidity levels. As a result, the city remained shrouded in fog and cloud throughout the day. According to the Meteorological Department, similar conditions are likely to prevail in Delhi, NCR till Sunday.Visibility at the Indira Gandhi International Airport started dipping around 11.20 p.m. on Monday, when low visibility procedures were implemented.The airport witnessed near zero visibility between 5.30 a.m. and 6.30 a.m. on Tuesday, but the condition started improving later allowing flight movement. Though general visibility remained below 800 metres for almost the entire day, there were no massive flight disruptions.“On Tuesday, persistent fog cover brought the day temperature down to 15.7 degrees Celsius, making it the second lowest maximum temperature of the season. Very high humidity and colder temperature prevailed on Tuesday across Delhi NCR, Chandigarh and Agra, which continued to keep moderate to dense fog covers at surface all day over this region. It is the longest fog cover in this season so far,” said Dr. R.K. Jenamani, Director-in-Charge, Airport weather unit. “In fact, in Delhi-NCR, it is the only day in this season so far when even afternoon peak warmer timing had moderate fog cover.”The dense fog also disrupted railway’s schedule. According to Northern Railway, 19 Delhi-bound trains, including Howrah Duronto, Sealdah Duronto and Kanpur Shatabdi were running late by several hours due to bad weather condition.Fifty-one trains were cancelled due to the fog.